## üéØ Research Philosophy: The Integration Challenge

Biology operates at the intersection of **complexity** and **precision**. Cellular processes occur under extreme molecular crowding (300-400 mg/mL) and spatial confinement, yet traditional biochemistry studies proteins in dilute conditions (1-10 mg/mL) that fail to capture this reality.

**My Vision:** Build integrated experimental platforms that recreate physiological constraints while maintaining single-molecule resolution.

